        "body": "this is a theorem which is used in defining shifted Legendre Polynomial.\r\n",
        "changedFiles": 1,
        "closed": false,
        "closedAt": null,
        "comments": {
          "nodes": [
            {
              "id": "IC_kwDOFcwZ1c6QKPG1",
              "body": "### PR summary [580d2b3460](https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/pull/17853/commits/580d2b34607e33e82db2898a9ac4bb2ac9c526e5)\n\n#### Import changes for modified files\n\nNo significant changes to the import graph\n\n\n<details><summary>Import changes for all files</summary>\n\n|Files|Import difference|\n|-|-|\n\n</details>\n\n---\n\n#### Declarations diff\n\n`+ iterate_derivative_finset_sum`\n<details>\n  <summary>You can run this locally as follows</summary>\n\n\n```bash\n## summary with just the declaration names:\n./scripts/declarations_diff.sh <optional_commit>\n\n## more verbose report:\n./scripts/declarations_diff.sh long <optional_commit>\n```\n</details>\n\nThe doc-module for `script/declarations_diff.sh` contains some details about this script.",
              "createdAt": "2024-10-17T06:10:57Z",
              "author": {
                "login": "github-actions"
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "IC_kwDOFcwZ1c6QKwK4",
              "body": "> Looks like that this result only uses the linearity of `derivative^[k]`. Maybe if you write `(h m) • ((- 1) ^ m : R[X]) * X ^ (k + m)` as `C (h m * (-1) ^ m) * X ^ (k + m)` then it can be solve by the linearity of `derivative^[k]` (I'm not sure which theorem it is) and `Polynomial.iterate_derivative_C_mul`.\r\n> \r\n> Maybe you can try `derivative ^ k` instead of `derivative^[k]`, the former is a linear map, but the latter is not; when apply to polynomials, these two are definitionally equal.\r\n\r\nok! thank you for your suggestion. But I see that `derivative^[k] `is used in the front of the document. I'm not sure if I want to change it to `derivative ^ k`?",
              "createdAt": "2024-10-17T07:09:47Z",
              "author": {
                "login": "ahhwuhu"
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "IC_kwDOFcwZ1c6QK-ei",
              "body": "I'm sorry, it's not `change` but you need to rw `LinearMap.pow_apply`. This code will work (note that I slightly changed your statement):\r\n```lean\r\ntheorem iterate_derivative_finset_sum (k : ℕ) (h : ℕ → ℕ) :\r\n    derivative^[k] (∑ m in Finset.range (k + 1), C (h m * (-1) ^ m : R) * X ^ (k + m)) =\r\n    ∑ m in Finset.range (k + 1), C (h m * (-1) ^ m : R) * derivative^[k] (X ^ (k + m)) := by\r\n  simp_rw [← LinearMap.pow_apply, map_sum, LinearMap.pow_apply, iterate_derivative_C_mul]\r\n```\r\nMy suggestion is add a generic result (for example, `iterate_derivative_sum`, which is similar to `map_sum`, and you can put this result next to [Polynomial.derivative_sum](https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/Algebra/Polynomial/Derivative.html#Polynomial.derivative_sum)) to mathlib, and the result you want is easily proved by this result. Don't add results which has very few use cases.",
              "createdAt": "2024-10-17T07:40:29Z",
              "author": {
                "login": "acmepjz"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
