              "createdAt": "2024-10-17T07:40:29Z",
              "body": "I'm sorry, it's not `change` but you need to rw `LinearMap.pow_apply`. This code will work (note that I slightly changed your statement):\r\n```lean\r\ntheorem iterate_derivative_finset_sum (k : ℕ) (h : ℕ → ℕ) :\r\n    derivative^[k] (∑ m in Finset.range (k + 1), C (h m * (-1) ^ m : R) * X ^ (k + m)) =\r\n    ∑ m in Finset.range (k + 1), C (h m * (-1) ^ m : R) * derivative^[k] (X ^ (k + m)) := by\r\n  simp_rw [← LinearMap.pow_apply, map_sum, LinearMap.pow_apply, iterate_derivative_C_mul]\r\n```\r\nMy suggestion is add a generic result (for example, `iterate_derivative_sum`, which is similar to `map_sum`, and you can put this result next to [Polynomial.derivative_sum](https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/Algebra/Polynomial/Derivative.html#Polynomial.derivative_sum)) to mathlib, and the result you want is easily proved by this result. Don't add results which has very few use cases.",
